Vasco Chaya LIFESTYLE WRITER chayav@dailynews.co.z AT LEAST 15 musicians have collaborated on an Oliver Mtukudzi tribute single titled Tribute to Tuku which is accompanied by a video. In the song, artists that include Terry Afrika, Anold Gara, Tsotsi, Comic Pastor, Mzimba, King James, Lazzie T, Mannex and Lutah King narrate different experiences they had with the late legendary musician.  Popularly known as Samanyanga, Mtukudzi died in 2018 at the age of 66. He became the first musician to be accorded hero status by the government. He was buried in his rural home in Madziwa just outside the Mashonaland Central provincial capital of Bindura. Mtukudzi, who had 66 studio albums to his name, also established a multi-million dollar arts centre, Pakare Paye, in Norton. Some of the musicians he collaborated with locally are Gary Tight, Mathias Mhere, Suluman Chimbetu, Tryson Chimbetu, Winky D, Ex Q, Reverend Togarepi Chivaviro and Fungisai Zvakavapano-Mashavave.   googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1588599181508-1'); });